      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 509: `placeCall` now runs before the call view controller is presented/registered via `present(... withStateable:)`. If `placeCall` emits synchronous or very early state changes, the UI/stateable observer can miss the initial call state or failure state. A safer latency optimization is to register/present the stateable first, then start the daemon call before modal dismissal/navigation work, or ensure the view model buffers and replays the current state when presentation completes.",
