      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 176: Dispatching `addOrUpdateCall(... notifyIncoming: true)` asynchronously can make the incoming-call notification race with later call-state callbacks. If the caller cancels quickly, a subsequent ended/removed event may be processed before this closure, and then this delayed closure can re-create or notify an incoming call that is already gone. Keep the state transition ordered on the same serialization path used by the other call-state mutations, or re-check that the call is still active/incoming before notifying inside the barrier.",
      "revId": "edfe7b5d48e8ceb4058c8c9dd2f0b8849c146e38",
